@Node coto "The purpose of this program"

@{b} What's this? @{ub}

    @{"I" Link autor} always have been interested in how to write programs.
    And this what are you looking at, is the first try to write something more
    than a window with text in it.
    I wanted this program to work in every environment and on different types of
    hardware, but before you drag me through the mud, because it doesn't work
    correctly, keep in mind, that this is my first try, and I hope not last. :)
    And if there is a bug, which really annoys you, don't hesitate and contact me -
    I'll be grateful for any suggestions or bug reports.

    This program is a decimal, hexadecimal, octavo numbers converter ...and that's
    all I think can be written about it's purpose...

    The program opens it's own public window, and "System Friendly".
    HexCon should run on any Amiga
    because of its @{"requirements" Link zctsj} - at least I hope it does... :)

    If you use this program send Email to me ;)

@EndNode

@Node zctsj "Requirements"

@{b} Requirements @{ub}

    Generally, nothing special:

    - 68020 processor :)
    - Kickstart 2.04 (OS 3.0 for localization and gadget help)
    - wizard.library

@EndNode

@Node jtsj "Usage"

@{b} Usage @{ub}

    The program is so primitive, that only few of the functions need to
    be explained.

    You can move through by using folds at the top of the window.

    Small icons on the right are used to copy the number in the field
    to Clipboard, from where it can be easily pasted (RIGHT AMIGA + V)
    wherever it is needed.

    An arrow at the bottom of the window recalls last entered number.
    (It recalls numbers in all folds)

    If you want to change the position of the window, or its size, it can
    be done by the following tooltypes:

    - WINL: Window's 'X' coordinate counted from its top left side.
    - WINT: The same as above, but for the 'Y'.

    - WINW: Width of the opened window.
    - WINH: Height of the opened window.

    There is a number of other tooltypes, wchich need to be modified manually,
    or through a menu:

    - CLIPUNIT: Defines Clipboard's unit (default: 0)
    - REFRESH: SMART / SIMPLE ...
    - MIN: Minimal size of window.
    - CHECK = (ON/OFF) - checks data correctness
    - CUT = (ON/OFF) - cuts binary values
    - REVERSE = (ON/OFF) - reverses entries order for the third fold

@EndNode

